<p><b>What is an engineering workshop manual?</b> A workshop manual, also known as a service manual, is a comprehensive guide that provides detailed information on how to repair and maintain a specific product or machine. These manuals are typically used by professionals in a particular industry, such as mechanics, technicians, or engineers.</p>
<p><b>What is the basic concept of workshop?</b> A workshop is an interactive meeting in which a group of people goes through a series of activities to achieve to solve a problem or work on a project. Workshops are often led by a facilitator and can range from a couple of hours to multiple days. This is our go-to definition of a workshop.</p>
